UML:TaggedValue.value: What the patient is going to take. Could be different from the PrescribedDose as far: - The medicine purchased is not identical to the prescribed one, but equivalent, so there is a difference of the names although the same ingredients and effect - The IntakeTime is more specific as compared with the general Frequency
The amount of medicine to be taken
Verbose description of how often the dose should be taken (once a day, 3 times before meal, ...) optional
Current precautions for the specific user as derived from the Incompliances and SideEffects attributes of all prescribed medicines
reference to the doctor, who suspended the prescription
Date on which the prescription is made invalid (due to various reasons of the doctor)
List of incompliances for this medicine
a reference to the prescribed medicine in case the pharmacist has provided an alternative brand
